name: fumarate reductase complex
description: "A membrane-bound flavoenzyme complex consisting of four subunits, A, B, C, and D. Fumarate reductase couples the reduction of fumarate to succinate to the oxidation of quinol to quinone, in a reaction opposite to that catalyzed by the related complex II of the respiratory chain (succinate dehydrogenase-(ubiquinone))."
